1
00:00:01,110 --> 00:00:06,390
When a market makes a strong move on volume,
this means that the price movement is confirmed

2
00:00:06,390 --> 00:00:08,660
by a simultaneous rise in volume.

3
00:00:08,660 --> 00:00:10,900
So volume means strength.

4
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:15,790
Volume must increase as the trend develops,
whether it is a bull or bear market.

5
00:00:15,790 --> 00:00:21,830
But what if you combine a moving average and
the volume in order read the market momentum

6
00:00:21,830 --> 00:00:24,110
or to analyze a breakout strength.

7
00:00:24,110 --> 00:00:28,050
Would this tool help you make better decisions
when trading or investing?

8
00:00:28,050 --> 00:00:32,910
Sure it can, and this tool is called volume
weighted moving average.

9
00:00:32,910 --> 00:00:37,220
So today we’ll talk about the volume weighted
moving average, you’ll learn the importance

10
00:00:37,220 --> 00:00:41,570
of using it and I’ll show you how to use
it in a trading strategy.

11
00:00:41,570 --> 00:00:47,140
Before we continue, if you are new to my channel,
make sure you subscribe, turn on the notifications

12
00:00:47,140 --> 00:00:51,590
and leave a like to show your support.

13
00:00:51,590 --> 00:00:56,630
The volume weighted moving average is a moving
average indicator which includes volume in

14
00:00:56,630 --> 00:00:58,239
its calculation.

15
00:00:58,239 --> 00:01:04,400
This moving average places more importance
on the closing prices which had a higher volume.

16
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:10,409
It incorporates not only the last number of
periods of price into its calculation but

17
00:01:10,409 --> 00:01:13,520
also the average volume during those periods.

18
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:19,160
The volume-weighted moving average (VWMA)
emphasizes volume by weighting prices based

19
00:01:19,160 --> 00:01:23,380
on the amount of trading activity in a given
period of time.

20
00:01:23,380 --> 00:01:29,660
Prices with heavy trading activity get more
weight than prices with light trading activity.

21
00:01:29,660 --> 00:01:34,190
This is very important information because
you can make better decisions when you add

22
00:01:34,190 --> 00:01:37,890
volume into your trading strategy.

23
00:01:37,890 --> 00:01:42,340
You could read the volume weighted moving
average in a similar manner to other moving

24
00:01:42,340 --> 00:01:43,340
averages.

25
00:01:43,340 --> 00:01:48,049
Its main use, however, arises when it is used
in conjunction with a SMA.

26
00:01:48,049 --> 00:01:55,540
So, let’s analyze a chart with a 50 SMA
and a 50 volume weighted moving average.

27
00:01:55,540 --> 00:01:59,829
At a first glance, you will see that they
pretty much follow the same trajectory.

28
00:01:59,829 --> 00:02:06,729
However, on further analysis, you will notice
the averages don’t mirror each other exactly.

29
00:02:06,729 --> 00:02:12,130
The reason for this, as I previously said,
is because the volume weighted ma emphasizes

30
00:02:12,130 --> 00:02:18,910
volume, while the SMA only factors the average
of the closing price per period.

31
00:02:18,910 --> 00:02:24,480
So, if you pay attention at the volume at
the bottom of the screen you will notice that

32
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:30,090
when we have a big volume candlestick, the
volume weighted moving average starts moving

33
00:02:30,090 --> 00:02:33,700
away from the trajectory of the simple moving
average.

34
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:39,290
Then, when we have lower market volumes, the
simple moving average and the volume weighted

35
00:02:39,290 --> 00:02:42,800
moving average are very close in value.

36
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:49,170
When the volume is stronger, the volume weighted
moving average will follow price more closely,

37
00:02:49,170 --> 00:02:55,599
and when volume decreases, it will mimic a
simple moving average.

38
00:02:55,599 --> 00:03:01,709
When the 50 volume weighted moving average
is between price and the 50 simple moving

39
00:03:01,709 --> 00:03:06,660
average SMA(50), then volume confirms we are
trending in that direction.

40
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:07,750
Look at this example.

41
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:14,150
At the exact moment of the breakout, the volume
weighted moving average was well above the

42
00:03:14,150 --> 00:03:20,319
SMA already, showing us that volume confirms
the uptrend.

43
00:03:20,319 --> 00:03:26,260
The retrace even bounced off from the volume
weighted moving average instead of the SMA

44
00:03:26,260 --> 00:03:28,360
as support.

45
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:32,209
So, how do you read the volume weighted moving
average?

46
00:03:32,209 --> 00:03:39,250
A volume weighted ma moving below an simple
moving average indicates bearish conditions.

47
00:03:39,250 --> 00:03:45,379
So, if the volume weighted moving average
crosses below the simple moving average, this

48
00:03:45,379 --> 00:03:49,210
implies that a bearish move is on the horizon.

49
00:03:49,210 --> 00:03:53,500
This could lead to a weakening in the bullish
trend or a possible reversal.

50
00:03:53,500 --> 00:04:00,980
If the price is able to break through both
the volume weighted ma and the SMA a bearish

51
00:04:00,980 --> 00:04:05,819
trend is confirmed and you can start searching
for short positions.

52
00:04:05,819 --> 00:04:12,730
A volume weighted ma above an SMA indicates
bullish conditions.

53
00:04:12,730 --> 00:04:18,629
So, if the volume weighted moving average
moves above the simple moving average, a bullish

54
00:04:18,629 --> 00:04:21,529
trend change is likely.

55
00:04:21,529 --> 00:04:28,819
Once the price is able to break both the volume
weighted ma and the SMA to the upside, you

56
00:04:28,819 --> 00:04:34,500
can start searching for long opportunities.

57
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:41,569
Separation between a volume weighted ma and
the simple ma indicates a trending market.

58
00:04:41,569 --> 00:04:47,009
In other words, if the volume weighted moving
average is between the chart and the simple

59
00:04:47,009 --> 00:04:50,780
moving average, then we have a signal for
a trending market.

60
00:04:50,780 --> 00:04:56,659
Keep in mind that sometimes the volume weighted
moving average will test the simple moving

61
00:04:56,659 --> 00:05:02,960
average as a support and resistance, depending
on the primary direction of the traded instrument.

62
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:06,919
These tests can be considered as potential
trend reversals.

63
00:05:06,919 --> 00:05:12,879
It doesn’t mean that the market will reverse,
it may continue its direction, like in this

64
00:05:12,879 --> 00:05:18,979
example, you just have to pay attention to
possible turning points.

65
00:05:18,979 --> 00:05:24,240
Both moving averages closer together might
suggest an exit point.

66
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:27,710
This signal is pretty much the opposite of
the previous one.

67
00:05:27,710 --> 00:05:31,240
You look for a contrary signal to the primary
trend.

68
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:37,369
For example, you have taken a long position
and you notice no separation between the volume

69
00:05:37,369 --> 00:05:41,089
weighted ma and the simple ma.

70
00:05:41,089 --> 00:05:46,210
This is the moment where you might want to
consider exiting the market and to collecting

71
00:05:46,210 --> 00:05:47,439
your profits.

72
00:05:47,439 --> 00:05:53,830
Now, let’s see how you could use the volume
weighted ma by its own, without the simple

73
00:05:53,830 --> 00:05:59,250
ma
First, to identify and confirm market trend

74
00:05:59,250 --> 00:06:03,889
If you want to trade in the direction of the
prevailing trend on the market, a volume weighted

75
00:06:03,889 --> 00:06:06,659
ma can offer some important clues.

76
00:06:06,659 --> 00:06:11,849
However, don’t forget that a moving average
is a lagging indicator, so it doesn’t predict

77
00:06:11,849 --> 00:06:16,789
new trends, just confirms the market trends
once they have been developed.

78
00:06:16,789 --> 00:06:20,230
So how you find and confirm trends with the
volume weighted ma:

79
00:06:20,230 --> 00:06:27,149
A possible uptrend is when the price is above
a moving average and the slope of the moving

80
00:06:27,149 --> 00:06:32,279
average is upward
A possible downtrend is when the price is

81
00:06:32,279 --> 00:06:37,009
below the moving average and its slope is
downward

82
00:06:37,009 --> 00:06:41,800
The slope of volume weighted ma is simply
the direction of the moving average plotted

83
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:44,589
on the chart.

84
00:06:44,589 --> 00:06:49,679
Another way to trade using volume weighted
moving averages is to look at them as dynamic

85
00:06:49,679 --> 00:06:51,020
support and resistance.

86
00:06:51,020 --> 00:06:57,370
They are referred to as dynamic because they
are not like the traditional support and resistance

87
00:06:57,370 --> 00:06:59,430
lines on the chart.

88
00:06:59,430 --> 00:07:02,229
They tend to change as price changes.

89
00:07:02,229 --> 00:07:07,979
Being so common and followed by so many people,
we can often see on charts that the price

90
00:07:07,979 --> 00:07:14,330
often stalls or bounces when hitting popular
moving averages.

91
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:19,199
Although volume weighted moving averages are
not like the normal support and resistance,

92
00:07:19,199 --> 00:07:21,990
they tend to behave the same way.

93
00:07:21,990 --> 00:07:27,360
As price stays below the volume weighted moving
average several times, it shows high selling

94
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:29,550
pressure in the market.

95
00:07:29,550 --> 00:07:34,789
As the price finds it hard to break through,
it means that the sellers are stronger than

96
00:07:34,789 --> 00:07:36,249
buyers.

97
00:07:36,249 --> 00:07:41,869
The volume weighted moving average above the
price becomes a resistance and price is likely

98
00:07:41,869 --> 00:07:45,680
to bounce back offering short opportunities.

99
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:52,099
Likewise when price stays above at the volume
weighted moving average, it becomes a support

100
00:07:52,099 --> 00:07:59,199
and therefore is likely to bounce back, offering
buy opportunities.

101
00:07:59,199 --> 00:08:04,949
Like any other support and resistance level,
price cannot hold forever, and sometimes these

102
00:08:04,949 --> 00:08:08,860
levels are violated and price breaks through.

103
00:08:08,860 --> 00:08:13,699
You can also take advantage of a strong break
below or above the volume weighted moving

104
00:08:13,699 --> 00:08:15,280
average to trade a breakout.

105
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:21,949
A classic way to trade a break out is to wait
for a price retest after the break, to avoid

106
00:08:21,949 --> 00:08:23,460
a fake out.

107
00:08:23,460 --> 00:08:29,479
Another strategy for overcoming the problem
with false signals is to wait a certain number

108
00:08:29,479 --> 00:08:34,719
of candles after the moving average line has
been crossed by the price before you enter

109
00:08:34,719 --> 00:08:35,780
your trade.

110
00:08:35,780 --> 00:08:42,099
This way, you filter out a lot of the choppy
price movements during times when the market

111
00:08:42,099 --> 00:08:45,680
is not showing any clear direction.

112
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:50,740
Volume weighted moving average helps a lot
to smooth out price action.

113
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:56,190
What you need to know is that the longer the
moving average, the smother it becomes and

114
00:08:56,190 --> 00:09:00,220
the slower it gets to reacting to price movements.

115
00:09:00,220 --> 00:09:07,130
Also, the shorter the moving average the choppier
it gets and the quicker it reacts to price

116
00:09:07,130 --> 00:09:08,130
movements.

117
00:09:08,130 --> 00:09:13,240
In a fast-moving trend, you will want to use
a faster moving average, in a slow-moving

118
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:18,019
trend, a slower moving average sometimes works
better.

119
00:09:18,019 --> 00:09:22,550
You can set the length of the moving average
to suit your trading style.

120
00:09:22,550 --> 00:09:28,140
Just remember that prices with heavy trading
activity get more weight than prices with

121
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:31,830
light trading activity.

122
00:09:31,830 --> 00:09:37,269
The volume weighted moving average is suited
to trend following strategies, because this

123
00:09:37,269 --> 00:09:41,120
indicator performs best in trending markets.

124
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:46,620
You can also use the volume weighted moving
in combination with other signals and techniques,

125
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:50,180
to get a more comprehensive analysis of the
market.

126
00:09:50,180 --> 00:09:56,040
Now, if you got value from this this video
or learned something new, make sure you subscribe,

127
00:09:56,040 --> 00:10:00,889
turn on the notifications so you don’t miss
future uploads and leave us a like to show

128
00:10:00,889 --> 00:10:02,610
your support.

129
00:10:02,610 --> 00:10:03,189
Until next time.

